title: Various Artists - Fireworking [trip-hop]
description:
This is a compilation I did this time last year. It was posted initially on a small forum and now you can hear it here. Well, more exactly, this is a slightly different version, in which track 11 - "Opium" by Jute - was replaced by another Jute song, due to the fact that the mix can't have two climaxes, one after another (thanks to "Flooded", it is already dizzy enough). Also, the first track - "Dancing On the Moon Within My Shoes" by Lost Balance - was replaced by another Lost Balance track, "Tunefull", which, in my opinion, stands better as a first track...
In the meantime, I have done lots of other compilations where you can also hear some of these songs, so forgive me if you've been watching my comps for a while... (I would like though to make soon a volume from Caferino Albuquerque with enough songs from artists I haven't featured before)

Happy New Year!
